main event: A civilian reported sighting a round object behind trees in Westerville, Ohio on May 30, 1966.
interesting points: The object was comparable to a star-like object in the sky., The observation lasted for 10 minutes., The object appeared to go behind trees during the observation., Civilian aircraft were noted in the area potentially explaining the sighting., The object was described as being round and light-colored.
sighted object: a round object comparable to a star
